Shadows Reforged

By Guillaume Lessard

The shadows rise again in this pulse-pounding sequel to Crossroads of Shadows.

Lisa Hawthorne thought the war was finished. After dismantling the Circle‚Äôs vast network and destroying the Resonance Protocol, she longed for peace and a return to normal life. But when whispers of a new threat surface, she and her fractured team are pulled back into a deadly conflict. This time, the stakes are higher than ever.

A devastating weapon known as the Shadow Core has emerged, capable of bringing the world to its knees. The remnants of the Circle are more dangerous than ever before, willing to unleash destruction on a global scale. From the bustling streets of Paris to the icy wilderness of Greenland, Lisa and her allies must race against time to dismantle hidden Nexuses and stop a terrifying contingency plan before it reshapes the future of humanity.

But the greatest battle may not be against the enemy. Within the team, old wounds reopen, trust is broken, and alliances fracture. Signalfall is a gripping techno legal thriller that blends cyber suspense with courtroom drama and hard science fiction. It follows Lisa Hawthorne, a brilliant engineer and whistleblower, as she races through rain-soaked Riga to collect evidence that could topple Nexus, a global surveillance system. The stakes are enormous: corporations and governments are colluding to trade our privacy for profit. To fight back, Lisa teams up with Alex, a resourceful hacker, and her father Jack, an environmental lawyer, and together they must reveal the truth before the courts are manipulated by powerful interests.

Across a globe-spanning narrative that moves from clandestine docks and secret data havens to dramatic trials, Signalfall explores real-world issues of data rights, encryption, whistleblowing and civil liberties. It dramatizes the evolution of Nexus into Echo, a more insidious platform, and the birth of Beacon, a decentralized network designed to protect users instead of exploiting them. Guillaume Lessard‚Äôs vivid storytelling combines action, ethical dilemmas and futuristic technology to pose urgent questions: who controls the networks that record our lives, and can we build a connected future based on transparency and trust?

This novel will appeal to fans of cyber thrillers, legal dramas, dystopian fiction and anyone interested in the politics of technology. With its mix of suspense, romance and social commentary, Signalfall delivers an unforgettable reading experience and invites you to consider what happens when love, truth and the internet collide.
